iao_definition: ['A signal amplification function is a signal conversion function to inject energy into an input signal so as to produce an output signal with increased differential magnitude while also seeking to minimize increases in the signal to noise ratio. For example, to produce a 0.1 KW output signal from a 1 mW RMS input signal.']
label: ['signal amplification function']

label: ['environmental pollution']
